						<summary>

						<p>On a slab paved into the floor around the darga (mosque).</p>						

						<p>Sadāśivarāya [A.D. 1542-1576].</p>						

						<p>Damaged and undated.</p>						

						<p>Seems to record a gift of land for a garden to the goddess Aṁkāladēvamma, probably by the donor Timmayadeva-mahārāja mentioned in the inscription (No. 292- A.R. No. 60 of 1956-57).</p>						

